divs: Sighting DetailsWent out to observe the flyover of the International Space Station. It was due to come by at 7:24pm along with the space shuttle over Scranton, PA. My wife, daughter, and I saw 2 circular, somewhat bright,starlike objets moving at an insane rate of speed, appearing to chase each other while traveling. We assumed it was the Space Station, checked the time, and it was 7:21pm. After pondering this for a few seconds, I realized that it couldn't have been the Space Station or Shuttle, because of the high rate of speed. We then saw the Station & Shuttle fly over more to the southwest at 7:24pm and at nowhere near the same rate of speed as the first objects. Thank You!
